Commentary.Commentary: We are set to get underway on Day 2 then! The umpires make their way out to the middle, as the Pakistan players are in a huddle near the ropes. Strategizing going on where Rizwan is imparting the final words. Done with that, they move on to take their respective positions on the field. New Zealand openers, Tom Latham and Tom Blundell also make their way out to the middle. Shaheen Afridi to begin with the ball. He can be a real menace on this wicket. Here we go...

Younis Khan, the batting coach of the Pakistanis, is up for a chat as well. He says that he his happy with the first innings total, especially after they had lost the toss. Chuckles and says that as a batting coach, he would have preferred 50 or more runs (admitting though that every batting coach is like that) but is still happy with this. Reckons that Azhar Ali played really well and that he played through the line, and that is important. States that his side had 2-3 crucial partnerships. Felt that Rizwan-Azhar partnership could have gone a bit longer, but is still happy with what they have on board. Younis says that he talks with his lads in the net and adds that in Test cricket, one plays for their country and hence have some responsibilites. McCullum asks Khan as to whether the batsmen batting a little out of the crease, was it a plan? And Younis Khan says 'yes'. The batting coach states that it was mainly to negate swing. YK goes onto add that any session, the first 6 balls need to be watched well. The Pakistani coach also emphasizes that 'leaving the ball' was an important aspect which they discussed. States that players like Faheem and Gohar are young in these conditions, but not young to him, as he has seen them before as well.

BJ Watling is caught up for a chat, he reckons Day 1 was an even day. He also states that last year they played India on a quicker wicket. BJ says that keeping is very individual and that one should do it however they feel like. Adds that keeping is a bit of a challenge at Hagley Oval as a lot of the balls bounce to near the face. Reckons that Day 1 witnessed a bit of tennis-ball like bounce.

Hello and welcome to Day 2 of the 2nd Test between New Zealand and Pakistan. The hosts have their noses in the front after bowling out Pakistan towards the end of Day 1. But then, Pakistan also did well to post a total close to 300, giving their bowlers something good to bowl at. The visitors however know that they cannot sit on that alone as the New Zealanders are very strong in their backyard. A couple of quick wickets would be the Pakistanis' respite against a strong Kiwi batting line-up. It will be interesting to see if the hosts can negotiate out the first session safely. Let us find out how it pans out as we get underway in just a short while...
.... Day 2, Session 1 ...

That's it from the First Day of this second Test. New Zealand would be a happy bunch of players as they have bundled out Pakistan for 297 and cometh Day 2 they would look to bat it out and wipe out the lead with minimal damage and then they would look to amass a lead. We will get to know how the day pans out on 4th January 2021. The action starts at 1100 local (2200 GMT). Till then, cheers and take care.

New Zealand's bowling was spot on as they used just 5 bowlers. The stand out performer for them was Kyle Jamieson who went onto take his third Test 5-wicket haul. Boult and Southee bagged a couple of wickets too. Matt Henry coming back into the side was a bit wayward at the start. He later went onto make a comeback with the ball as he scalped an all-important wicket of Azhar Ali. A few dropped catches and a few edges not carrying summed up the day for New Zealand.

Azhar Ali, though continued to hold the fort at one end as Pakistan skipper, Mohammad Rizwan joined hands with his number 3 batsman and started the rebuilding act. The duo soon started rotating the strike and soon went onto find the odd boundaries in the process but went past their respective fifties. They were going well with an 88-run stand when Rizwan departed. Azhar Ali despite fighting it hard all day for his runs, departed for 93. Faheem Ashraf once again proved his mettle with the bat when he smashed 48 runs and newcomer debutant Zafar Gohar smashed 34 runs.

It all started with New Zealand winning the toss and putting Pakistan to bat. The visitors though did not start the way they would have liked as they lost Shan Masood for a duck. Then, a 62-run stand between Abid Ali and Azhar Ali revived their batting to some extent before Abid Ali departed. Soon after Haris Sohail, who has had a poor outing in the Test series so far followed him and Fawad Alam was the next one to depart.

What a day of Test cricket we have had. Brilliant bowling, good batting and good lower-order resistance and to cap of the day, rain too paid a visit. New Zealand would be a bit happier as they have castled Pakistan for 297 runs.

So, having done well after being reduced to 88/4 Pakistan would look to capitalise on this platform with Azhar Ali out there playing in 90 and just 10 runs shy off what could be a well-deserved ton. Faheem Ashraf can bat briskly and Pakistan would hope these two to continue. Whereas, New Zealand would hope for a couple of quick wickets to get into the tail of Pakistan batting. How will the session go? Join us after this short break to know more.

New Zealand's bowling was tight as usual though Southee and Boult went for a few when they were looking for some swing after the rain break. The stand out performer though was Kyle Jamieson who once again broke the crucial stand to hand New Zealand the advantage. Henry in his comeback game looked a bit off colour but he could have had a wicket to his name had Ross Taylor held onto one in the slips.

A brilliant session for the visitors. Resuming their innings on 88/4, Pakistan started counter-attack with Azhar Ali and Mohammad Rizwan out there in the middle. A couple of rain breaks though halted their charge but they continued to rotate the strike and get the odd boundary when the play resumed. In the process, Rizwan went past his fifty as the duo stitched a 50-run stand. Just when it seemed that both these batsmen would continue for Pakistan, an absolute ripper from Jamieson claimed the skipper of Pakistan. Though Azhar Ali continued to play his part as he added runs from one end.
Another fruitful session of a Test comes to an end. As Pakistan score 130 runs for the loss of just one wicket.

Done and dusted with the National Anthems. The New Zealand players are in a huddle as they get some final advice from their skipper. Shan Masood and Abid Ali will open the innings for Pakistan. Tim Southee will start the proceedings for New Zealand.
The players from both the teams walk out for their respective National Anthems. It will be Pakistan's first followed by New Zealand's.

Pitch Report - It is a pleasant climate reckons Craig McMillan. Brendon McCullum joins him and says that it is a good ground to bat as the surface looks good for batting. Brendon says that the true bounce of the pitch makes stroke-making a bit easier and if the batsmen are ready to play their shots they will get value for their shots.

New Zealand (Playing XI) - Tom Latham, Tom Blundell, Kane Williamson (C), Ross Taylor, Henry Nicholls, BJ Watling (WK), Daryl Mitchell (IN FOR MITCHELL SANTNER), Kyle Jamieson, Tim Southee, Matt Henry (IN FOR NEIL WAGNER), Trent Boult.

Pakistan (Playing XI) - Shan Masood, Abid Ali, Azhar Ali, Fawad Alam, Haris Sohail, Mohammad Rizwan (WK/C), Faheem Ashraf, Zafar Gohar (IN FOR YASIR SHAH), Mohammad Abbas, Shaheen Afridi, Naseem Shah.

Pakistan skipper, Mohammad Rizwan says that they too wanted to bowl first but the toss is not in their hand. So they will now try and do their best with the bat. Mentions that they are confident with how they played the last game and look to bring that spirit in this game too. Further he mentions that the bowlers and batsmen did well and he hopes they do it here too to square off the series. Ends by saying that Zafar Gohar will make his Test debut and he replaces Yasir Shah.

New Zealand skipper, Kane Williamson says that they will bowl first. Mentions that the surface looks good and it will have something for the bowlers early on. Further says that the outfield too looks to be fast. Ends by saying that they have had some good games against Pakistan in the past and they would look to play with full energy in the final Test of the summer. Informs that Matt Henry comes in for Neil Wagner and Daryl Mitchell comes in for Mitchell Santner.

TOSS - It's time for the flip of the coin at Hagley Oval, Christchurch. The two skippers, Kane Williamson and Mohammad Rizwan are out in the middle. Kane has the coin as he gives it a flip. Heads is the call from Mohammad Rizwan and it falls in favour of Williamson. NEW ZEALAND ELECT TO FIELD FIRST!

After a 101-run drubbing at the hands of New Zealand. Pakistan once again enter the field looking to square off the two-match series. Hello and welcome to our coverage of the 2nd Test between Pakistan and New Zealand which also turns out to be the first of the 2021 season. Babar-less Pakistan take on Wagner-less New Zealand. Having lost their commander to a fractured thumb, Pakistan are once again led by their second in command, Mohammad Rizwan. Whereas, New Zealand would be without the service of their main weapon, Neil Wagner who is out due to an injury. Having shown up a fight in the first Test Pakistan would look to go the distance this time around. It is a battle of Pakistan bowlers' adaptability to bowl on green tracks. Whereas, their batsmen would be against some quality pace attack. For New Zealand, the only headache would be whom to replace Neil Wagner with? Answers to all such questions coming up shortly at the toss. Stay tuned...

With Around 11 overs remaining in the day, Pakistan openers have a task in hand to see off the day without any damage. Whereas, New Zealand bowlers after a couple of days rest are raring to unleash themselves on the tired Pakistan batsman. They would look to take a wicket or two to cap of a brilliant day for them. Join us as Pakistan begin their second innings in a short while on the other side of the break.

Pakistan's bowling was a sorry state of affair as they conceded over 650 runs. Naseem Shah, Faheem Ashraf and Zafar Gohar all went in excess of 100 runs. Naseem though bowled 9 No Balls and 4 Wides. Afridi, Abbas and Ashraf were the only one in the wickets as they all took a couple each. Poor fielding and catching rubbed salt on their wounds as they dropped and dropped further under the mountain of runs. Overall a poor bowling display and an even shoddy display of fielding.

New Zealand's innings was all about Kane Williamson-Henry Nicholls stand as the duo stitched a 369-run stand to deflate and decimate Pakistan. The openers Latham and Blundell built a platform with a 52-run stand before they both departed. Taylor too could not do much in the middle. Then came the partnership which not only helped New Zealand get past New Zealand's total but extend a mighty lead over them too. The duo batted and batted and batted all day on Day 2 and almost full of Day 3. Nicholls scored his 7th Test ton while his skipper went onto score his 4th Test double ton. Both departed though but a new hero emerged in the form of Daryl Mitchell who went onto score his maiden Test ton to floor Pakistan completely. Jamieson played a handy knock too to escalate the lead beyond the 360-run mark.

Finally the declaration comes! Don't know Pakistan would be happy or sad seeing the declaration. With the lead of 362 runs, Pakistan are under a lot of pressure and upon that overcast conditions. A heck of a task for them to end the day on the right note with the bat though.

Another back of a length ball outside off, Henry slices it through cover-point for a single.
Short of good length outside off, Henry slaps it powerfully but fails to beat the fielder at covers.
Short and down the leg side, Henry is uninterested to play at it.
Ohh Williamson lucky there! Fuller and around off, Kane looks to defend it off the back foot but the ball takes the inside edge and rolls past the leg pole. The batsmen cross ends.
Fuller and around off, Kane drops it to gully with soft hands there.
Full on middle, driven through mid on for a single.
Tossed up outside off, Nicholls cuts it through point and gets to the other end with a single.
Flighted around off, Kane drives it through covers and gets a run.
Floated on off, driven towards long on for a single.
A full toss outside off, Henry plays it back to the bowler.
Tossed up on off, KW strokes it to long off for a single.
Zafar Gohar to bowl from the other end. 13-0-56-0 are his figures so far.
On off, blocked towards mid off.
FOUR! Slapped away! Short and wide outside off, Henry throws the bat at it and gets it through point as the ball runs away to the fence there.
FOUR! Incredible! Short and around middle, Nicholls gets across his stumps and then helps it on its way towards the fine leg fence for a boundary.
A little too wide to make the batsman play there as Henry lets it be.
Length and outside off, HN leaves it alone.
Back of a length ball outside off, Kane slaps it through covers and gets the session going with a single.

We are back for the second session of Day 3. The Pakistan players are out in the middle. Kane Williamson and Henry Nicholls will resume their innings for New Zealand. There were a few drops of rain during the lunch break. Looking at the current conditions we might get a stop start session as rain is forecasted in the afternoon. Mohammad Abbas will start the proceedings for this session.
... Day 3, Session 2 ...

So, with the lead going over 100 runs. It is worrying signs for Pakistan. If they do not pick wickets then they could be playing the catch up role with a hefty lead in front of them. Will we see some turnaround in the post Lunch session or will New Zealand continue to steamroll Pakistan? Join us for the post Lunch session at 1340 Local (0040 GMT).

Pakistan's struggle with the ball continued as they failed to pick wickets. Their bowlers strayed all over the place as runs were leaked. Naseem Shah in particular was taken apart there. Afridi and Abbas too failed to contain the run flow. Ashraf who bowled well yesterday was also all over the place here. Frustration clearly showed in their bowling as runs were given easily. They look decimated completely out there and require some kind of motivation to get back into the game. Wickets are the key there which they have failed to get.

Another session going New Zealand's way. They started from where they left overnight. Though Nicholls is struggling with his calf but he has made sure to stay out there and assist his skipper in getting a good lead in the first innings. He too went onto score his 7th Test ton in the process. Kane Williamson, on the other hand, has gone about his business and he has cut, pulled, drove the balls to get a score in excess of 150 runs for himself. In the process he has gone past 7000 Test runs too. The partnership too crossed the 300-run mark as New Zealand's lead too crossed 100 runs.
On middle, Williamson drives it through mid on for a single. 400 up for New Zealand! THAT WILL BE LUNCH ON DAY 3!
Full on off, Nicholls pushes it through mid off for a single.
Short delivery outside off, Nicholls cuts it to point.
Floated delivery on off, Henry keeps it out.

Lucky! Flighted delivery on off, Nicholls goes way across his off stump as he looks to sweep but misses it. The ball goes in between his legs and past the leg stump towards short fine leg. This is what you call a lucky guy when even a false shot does not bring your downfall.
Tossed up delivery on middle, Williamson pushes it through mid on for a single.
Back of a length on off, Nicholls pushes it to point.
Length delivery on off, Nicholls guides it to gully.
Full ball on off, Nicholls drives it towards mid off.
Back of a length on off, Nicholls pushes it to covers.
Full delivery on off, Nicholls drives it to mid off.
Length ball outside off, Nicholls leaves it alone.
Shaheen Afridi comes back for his third spell this morning. 26-6-69-1 are his figures so far.
Outside off, Kane shoulders arms to this one.
On middle, Nicholls plays a reverse sweep through point. The batsmen cross ends. THE LEAD NOW STANDS AT EXACT 100 RUNS!
Full delivery on off, Williamson drives it through mid off for a single.
Short ball outside off, Nicholls cuts it towards point for a run.
Floated delivery on off, Nicholls looks to play the reverse sweep but gets hit on the pads.
Tossed up delivery on middle, Nicholls flicks it to mid-wicket.
Zafar Gohar is back on. 11-0-50-0 from him so far.
Good length delivery on off, Williamson looks to defend but gets an outside edge. It goes towards first slip where it falls short of the fielder.
On off, Williamson punches it to covers.
Length ball on off, Williamson guides it to gully.
Back of a length on middle, Nicholls flicks it through square leg for a single.
Length delivery on off, Nicholls defends it off the back foot.
FIVE WIDES! Short delivery down the leg side, Nicholls lets it go. It goes past the keeper towards fine leg for a boundary.
Bumper on off, Henry ducks under it.
WIDE! Bouncer on middle, Nicholls does well to duck under it.
On off, Kane pushes it towards the off side.
Back of a length on off, Williamson defends it back towards the bowler.
Good length delivery on off, Williamson blocks it off the back foot.
Full delivery on middle, Nicholls pushes it towards mid on for a quick single.
Length ball on off, Nicholls pushes it to mid off.
Full delivery on middle, Williamson flicks it through mid-wicket for a single. 150 for Kane Williamson!

DROPPED! Naseem Shah drops a tough chance! Short delivery on off, Nicholls says enough of ducking as he tries to flat bat it over the bowler. He though manages to get it off the bottom half of the bat as the ball lobs towards the bowler. Naseem there goes for the catch with one hand as he stretches his left hand out. The ball hits his fingertips and goes to his left side as he tries to take the rebound but fails to do so. Great effort from the young lad who is under the pump in this Test.
Bouncer on middle, Nicholls ducks under it.
Back of a length on middle, Nicholls defends it out.
Short delivery outside off, Nicholls lets it go.
Short ball outside off, Nicholls leaves it alone.
Length delivery on off, Williamson pushes it through point for a single.
Change of ends for Naseem Shah. He has so far conceded 100 runs in his 19 overs and bowled just a couple of maidens in that.
On off, Williamson guides it towards third man for a single.
Back of a length on middle, Kane keeps it out.
Good length delivery on off, Williamson defends it off the back foot.
Bouncer on middle, Williamson does well to duck under it.
Back of a length on off, Nicholls punches it through point for a single.
BEATEN! Full and outside off, Nicholls looks to drive but misses it.
Shaheen Afridi comes back on. 24-6-65-1 from him so far.
FOUR! That's whipped away! Doesn't matter where you bowl to this guy it ends up over the fence. Poor delivery from Ashraf! Full on leg, Williamson flicks it easily towards fine leg for a boundary.
Short again on middle, Williamson pulls it through mid-wicket. The fielder in the deep does well to stop it with a slide. The batsmen pick up a couple.
Short delivery on leg, Nicholls pulls it through square leg for a single.
Back of a length on off, Nicholls pushes it to point.
Length ball on off, Williamson guides it towards third man for a single.
Short delivery on off, Nicholls cuts it through point for a run.
Short delivery outside off, Williamson shoulders arms to this one.
Outside off, Williamson lets it go.
Good length delivery on off, Kane defends it off the back foot.
Back of a length outside off, Williamson offers no shot to this one.
FOUR! Class shot! Full on middle, Williamson drives it through mid on for a boundary. 300-run stand is up between Williamson and Nicholls!
Short of a length delivery on leg, Nicholls nudges it towards square leg for a single.
FOUR! That is caressed! Full delivery on off, Williamson drives it through covers for a boundary.
Outside off, Kane shoulders arms to this one.
Good length delivery on off, Williamson defends it off the back foot.
Back of a length on off, Williamson offers a solid defense on this one.
Full delivery on off, Williamson drives it to covers.
Good length delivery on off, Williamson defends it off the back foot.
Shah bowls a bouncer, Nicholls does well to duck under it.
Bumper on middle, Nicholls ducks under it.
Bouncer on middle, Henry does well to duck under it.
FOUR! Cracking shot! Short and outside off, Nicholls cuts it hard through point for a boundary.
Length delivery on off, Nicholls defends it out.
FOUR! That is put away! Short ball on leg, Nicholls pulls it towards fine leg for a boundary.
Full delivery on off, Williamson drives it to covers.
On a good length on off, Kane dabs it towards gully.
Back of a length on off, Williamson punches it to point.
Length delivery on off, Williamson blocks it off the front foot.
Good length delivery on middle, Williamson looks to defend but gets an inside edge on it. It goes past the stumps towards fine leg. The batsmen get two runs.
Full on middle, Williamson drives it through mid on. The fielder chases it and does well to stop it. The batsmen pick up a couple.
Full delivery on off, Nicholls drives it to covers.
Outside off, Nicholls does not bother to play at that.
Back of a length on off, Henry keeps it out.
FOUR! Lovely shot! Full delivery on off, Nicholls stays steady and then drives it through covers for a boundary.
Length delivery on off, Nicholls defends it off the back foot.
FOUR! Terrific shot! Back of a length on off, Nicholls stands tall and then punches it through point for a boundary. It though goes a bit uppish but in the gap there. THE LEAD IS NOW 51 RUNS!
WIDE! Bouncer on middle, Nicholls does well to duck under it.

DRINKS! It has been an excellent hour for New Zealand. 57 runs scored and not a wicket lost by them. Kane Williamson is looking strong and Nicholls has reached his hundred and is looking great out there. On the other hand, Pakistan bowlers need wickets to put pressure on New Zealand. They need to break this partnership as these two are slowly and steadily taking the game away from them. The lead is now 46 runs and with each passing over the lead keeps on getting fatter and fatter. Can Pakistan get the much-needed breakthrough after this small break? Let's find out as Naseem to continue.

An appeal for LBW but nothing from the umpire. Length ball angled into Kane, Williamson looks to tickle it towards the leg side but can only manage a faint inside edge onto pads. Pakistan players appeal but nothing doing from the umpire.
Fuller and around off, Kane plays it with soft hands as the ball catches the outside edge and rolls to the slip cordon.
On off, blocked out by Kane.
Length and around off, Henry tucks it to the leg side and gets a single. This is the highest ever 4th wicket partnership for New Zealand.

FOUR BYES! That reared off the pitch! Length and across the left hander, Nicholls sways away from the line of the ball. The ball keeps on going away as the keeper too fails to glove it. It goes to the third man region for a boundary, Byes signalled.
Length and outside off, left alone by Henry there.
Good length and slower too as Kane leaves it. The keeper too fails to collect it cleanly as it goes to the third man region. Two Byes taken.
Another length ball on off, Kane does not play at it.
Length and outside off, Kane makes a leave now.
Short delivery outside off, Williamson looks to cut but misses it.
Length ball on off, Williamson defends it off the back foot.
Good length delivery outside off, Williamson offers no shot to this one.
Outside off, left alone this time by Henry.
Beaten! Length and outside off, Henry goes for the drive and gets beaten comprehensively there.
Good length and on off, Nicholls defends it out.
Fuller and outside off, Henry carves it through covers and gets a couple as the fielder in the deep misfields there.
Fuller and on off, Henry plays it to mid on.
Length and on middle, kept out to the leg side.
Faheem Ashraf to bowl for the first time on Day 3.
A loose stroke from Kane there! Full and outside off, Williamson slashes at it but is lucky to not get an outside edge on that one.

FOUR! Just guided away! Good length and around off, Kane comes on the front foot then opens the face of the bat to guide it through gully as the ball reaches the third man fence for a boundary. Played with soft hands there by Kane.
Length ball on off, blocked out safely.
Length and around leg, Henry looks to tuck but gets it off the pads. It goes towards fine leg. The batsmen take a leg bye.
Fuller and on off, Nicholls drives it but finds covers.
Length and on off, driven through covers for a single.
Naseem Shah to bowl for the first time on Day 3.
SIX! A nice pickup shot from Henry! He goes all the way! Full and around off, Nicholls picks it and deposits it over the mid-wicket fence for a biggie. First one of the innings.
On a length and on middle, Kane tucks it towards mid-wicket and gets a single. 7000 Test runs for the Talismanic Kane Williamson!
Good length and on off, Kane tucks it to the leg side this time.
Fuller and around off, Kane blocks it from within the crease to mid on.
Outside off, left alone.
Length and down the leg side, Williamson looks to tickle it fine but misses it.
FOUR! That's cut away! Short and outside off, Henry cuts it through point uppishly and fetches a boundary there. 250-run stand is up between these two.
Short of good length on off, Henry hops and keeps it out to the off side this time.
Fuller and angled on off, Henry strokes it towards mid off now.
Length and around off, kept out by Henry there.
On off, played to mid on this time.
Length and outside off, Henry does not offer a shot. Hang on folks... NO BALL IT IS! Shaheen has overstepped reckons the third umpire. The onfield umpire signals a no ball there.
Fuller and on off, Williamson drives it to the wide of mid off fielder and calls for a quick run which he gets easily.
On off, kept out to covers.

FOUR! That is a 100 for Henry Nicholls! His 7th in the format! A knock filled with Grit and Guts! Fuller and outside off, Henry carves it through covers and the ball races to the fence to bring up the milestone for Henry there.
Another delivery which is outside off, Henry does not offer a shot to it.
Length ball angled across Henry, Nicholls lets it go through to the keeper.
Angles a length ball into the pads of Williamson who misses his flick as the ball rolls towards square leg for a single. A leg bye signalled.
Length and on off, kept out by Kane.
FOUR! Nicely done! Length and angled into Henry, Nicholls clips it nicely through backward square leg and gets a boundary.
Length on off, pushed back to the bowler who fields it.

A huge shout for LBW but the umpire is unmoved! Afridi angles one in the pads of Henry who fails to flick it. The ball hits him on the pads as the bowler appeals for LBW. Sensible not to review as it was going down leg anyway.
Full and on off, Kane drives it towards mid on and gets a single..
Length and outside off, Kane this time does a sensible thing as he leaves it.
Wide yorker outside off, Williamson looks to lay bat on ball but fails to do so.
Full delivery on off, Nicholls drives it to covers.

DROPPED! Azhar Ali is the culprit! Pakistan grass one more out there. It was meant to be taken but the fielder there fails to hold onto it. Length and wide outside off, Nicholls cuts it but the ball flies off the outside edge. It goes towards gully where the fielder goes for the catch but fails to grab it.
Good length ball outside off, Nicholls shoulders arms to this one.
Full again on off, Nicholls drives it through covers. The fielder chases it and does well to stop it. The batsmen get two runs.
Full on middle, Nicholls flicks it to mid-wicket.
Full delivery on off, Nicholls drives it to mid off.

FOUR! A couple of millimeters here and there and it could have been the end of Kane Williamson. Fuller and angled into Kane once again by Shaheen. Williamson clips it in the air but just wide of that leg slip fielder as the ball goes to the fine leg fence for a boundary. 300 comes up for NEW ZEALAND!

FOUR BYES ONCE AGAIN! Once again Shaheen lands one on a length and angles it into the batsman there, Kane misses his flick there as the keeper too fails once again to stop the ball. The ball goes into the fine leg fence. NEW ZEALAND INTO THE LEAD NOW! THEY LEAD BY 2 RUNS!

FOUR BYES! That beat everyone on its way to the fence! Length and angled into Kane there, Williamson looks to glance it down to fine leg but misses it. The keeper too fails to collect it as the ball goes to the fine leg fence.
Shaheen targets that top of off stump line as he bowls a length ball there but Kane defends it out too.
Another fuller length ball outside off, Kane shoulders arms to this one.
Length and angled on off, Kane is equally good to dead bat it off the front foot.
Fuller once again and around off, Henry comes on the front foot and then blocks it out towards mid off.
Fuller and outside off, Henry frees his arms and plays a good cover drive but finds the fielder there to perfection.
Length and across the left hander, Nicholls makes a leave this time.
Fuller and around off, Henry looks to play it to the leg side but misses it to get rapped high on the thigh pad.
Fuller and on off, Henry gets it off the toe-end of the bat there as the ball rolls behind point there.
Good length and around off, Nicholls brings out a solid front foot defense there.
Length and on off, Kane defends it out to point.
FOUR! That's a good shot! Williamson at his best! Afridi strays one on the pads, Williamson glances it past the short fine leg fielder and into the fence for a boundary.
Fuller and around off, Kane taps it to point now.
Short ball on middle, Kane sees it and then sits under it.
First runs of the morning! Henry moves into the 90s. Fuller and on off, Henry strokes it towards mid on and takes a single.
Length ball around off, Nicholls looks to tuck it to the leg side but gets in a tangle there as the ball hits him on the thigh pad.
Fuller length and on off, kept out this time to the on side.
Length and outside off, Kane watches the ball and then lets it sail through past him.
Good length and around off, Kane plays it with an angled bat and soft hands to gully.
Fuller and pushing the batsman on the back foot as Kane defends it out to the off side.
Good length and around off, Kane stands tall and defends it out once again off the back foot.
Fuller and around off, Kane stays glued on the back foot as he dead bats it.
Length and swinging away outside off, Henry offers no shot to it.
Good leave there! Length ball around off, Nicholls covers his sticks and then shoulders arms to it. Could have been in trouble had the ball jag backed in.
Full and around off, driven off the inner half of the bat towards mid on.
A swing and a miss! Short and wide outside off, Henry looks to cut it off the back foot but the ball goes past the outside edge as Nicholls fails to get bat on ball.
Gets it a bit closer to off pole as Henry blocks it out off the back foot.
Some swing for Shaheen there. He lands one on a length and outside off, the ball swings away further as Henry lets it go through to the keeper.
Shaheen Afridi to bowl from the other end. 19-5-45-1 are his figures so far.
A maiden to start! Abbas was right on the money in the over. He keeps bowling that good length line around off, Kane once again defends it out.
Slightly fuller once again, Kane defends it with soft hands towards gully.
Fuller and around off, Kane defends it by coming half-forward towards the leg side.
Another short of good length around off, Kane keeps it out off the back foot once again.
Good length and around off, Williamson blocks it off the back foot now.
Brilliantly fielded! Short and wide outside off, Kane cuts it but finds point fielder who does well to field it.

We are all set to begin Day 3. The Pakistan players are out in the middle. Kane Williamson and Henry Nicholls will resume their innings for New Zealand. Mohammad Abbas will start the proceedings for Day 3.

Pitch Report - Grant Elliott is down for the pitch report. He says that yesterday was hot so the conditions of the pitch changed a lot while today seems to be overcast and a bit breezy which means the ball will swing. He further informs that there is a chance of a drizzle later in the day.

Ross Taylor is down for a chat. Taylor says that after a lot of team discussion it was decided that Nicholls is ready to bat straightaway or he retire hurts now and then comes back later to bat. He ends by saying that he wants New Zealand to bat all day long and put Pakistan under pressure.

UPDATE - An update on Henry Nicholls who was struggling during the closing hours of Day 2 after he went for a run. Henry has sustained a calf strain but is cleared by the New Zealand medical team to continue to bat today.

If Day 2 was a one way traffic then Day 3 promises to be a cracker. Also known as the moving day in Test match we will soon find out which way the pendulum will swing. With the pitch quickening up a bit and the balls hurrying onto the bat makes it a Test of skills and character. Who will come out on top by the end of Day 3? Stay tuned as the action continues in a short while.

Pakistan are just looking at the end of the dark tunnel right now to get a ray of hope. No one is to blame but themselves after they displayed some shoddy fielding. Dropped catches, edges not going to the set field all happened on Day 2. Pakistan having taken the new ball would look to use it to their own advantage and pick wickets to control the lead and keep it to as small as possible.

Hello and welcome to Day 3 of this 2nd Test between New Zealand and Pakistan. New Zealand's trail is just 11 runs and they have 7 batsmen still available of which the pair of Kane Williamson and Henry Nicholls is still out there. The duo having added 215 runs are going strong at the moment. Though Nicholls had some issue during the closing hours on Day 2 but he looks fine to bat. New Zealand have their skipper batting at 112 while Henry is closing in on another Test ton of his own. They would look to bat out Pakistan by amassing a hefty lead.
... Day 3, Session 1 ...

So, a good hard day of Test cricket comes to an end. The New Zealanders will look to step out on Day 3, go past the deficit and will look to build on a healthy lead. They know that time is well on their side and will be in no hurry as they do so. But can the Men in Green begin Day 3 strongly and curtail that ambition of the Kiwis? We will find out on Tuesday, 5th January 2020, as we get underway for Day 3! Join us at 1100 Local (2200 GMT, THE PREVIOUS DAY) for the same and until then, take care and stay safe.

A tough day for the Pakistan bowlers. Afridi, Abbas and Faheem have a wicket each but more was expected from them, especially from the former two. Naseem and Zafar not only went wicketless, but went for plenty as well, by Test match standards. All in all, a challenging day for the Pakistanis, as they also dropped a few opportunites, both of Williamson and Nicholls, towards the end.

The Kiwis were then at 71/3 at the end of 30 overs. And just as Pakistan looked to be on top, the duo of Kane Williamson and Henry Nicholls took the momentum away from them. Their partnership is unbeaten still, at 215 runs, and it is the highest 4th wicket stand for the New Zealanders at Christchurch. They trail by just 11 runs now and have 7 wickets still in hand.

The New Zealanders started off the day strongly. The opening partnership was braving it well and looked to be going strong before Pakistan struck twice and in quick succession to remove both the openers. Then, Williamson and Ross braved it out till Lunch but Taylor did not last long once the 2nd session began.

A terrific partnership between Henry and Kane here. The former has an injury and it remains to be seen if he will step out on Day 3 but it has still been a very commendable partnership this. Has been New Zealand's day, this!
Shaheen finishes with a good length ball outside off, Henry does not want to chase after this and lets it through to the keeper. THAT WILL BE STUMPS ON DAY 2!
Another full ball down the leg side, Henry, once more, misses his tuck away to the leg side.
Down the leg side this time, HN misses his flick. Should be the last two deliveries of Day 2.
Full on leg, Kane tucks this to the fine leg region. Gets to the other end.
Another full delivery on middle, clipped to fine leg for a single. Nicholls moves to 89 now.
A full ball on the pads, Henry looks to tuck this one away but misses and the ball goes off his pads to the right of Rizwan, who dives and makes a good stop.
Another ball outside off, moves away after pitching, Williamson, again does not think twice and lets it through.
Length on off, Kane keeps this one out.
Outside off, left alone.

OUCHHH! That would have hurt, hit him right where it stings! A back of a length ball around off and middle, nips in slightly as Kane looked to block it away. He missed and the ball went onto hit him on his unmentionables. Kane shakes it off and is ready to face the next delivery.
Outside off, KW is happy to see this sail into Rizwan's gloves.
Length again, around off and middle, Kane pushes this to the mid-wicket region and yells 'no' for the single.
Outside off, well left alone by Henry. A maiden by Shaheen.
Third similar ball in a row, Nicholls does not play at this.
Similar delivery as the last ball, Henry again does not attempt to put bat to ball.
On a good length, just outside the off pole, Nicholls watchfully leaves this one.
On off, blocked to the leg side.
On a good length around the pads, Henry looks to tuck it away but misses and the ball comes off the pads to the leg side.
Outside off, KW offers no shot to this delivery.
Length delivery and around off, Williamson keeps this one out.
Down the leg side, KW misses his tuck away to the leg side. NZ still trail by 13 runs.
A back of a length delivery around off, Kane is solid in his defense. A loud 'no' follows as well, in regard to the single.
On off, tapped to point.
NO BALL. Outside off, Kane is well aware of his off pole as he leaves this one alone. The umpire also calls this as a No Ball as Abbas has overstepped.

Henry has asked for the physio here. And the New Zealand physio is out in the middle. Looks to be a bit more than cramp here. Nicholls is stretching himself out. Some strapping is happening on his leg. Right, Henry Nicholls seems to be good here. The pads are back on and he is set to continue.
On off, worked to the leg side for a single.
On middle, worked to mid on for a quick run.

EDGED...AND PUT DOWN! The skipper has put down this chance, should have been taken! Nicholls gets yet another life and this is very poor stuff from Rizwan. Shaheen continues to bowl on a length outside off, Nicholls chases after this one but he does not make clean contact and the ball takes the outside edge and goes to the left of Rizwan. He dives and grabs it as well but in the followthrough, he drops the ball. Should have been taken, this. Was not the toughest of chances. Henry, too, was annoyed as he went chasing after this.
On a length again this time, outside off, Nicholls raises his blade and lets this one through.
Another length delivery, but outside off this time, Henry does not want to have a poke at this.
Outside off, punched to the cover region.
Shaheen starts off with a good length delivery outside the off pole, Nicholls has no issues in letting this one go to the keeper.

Second new ball is due now. And looks like it has been taken straightaway. Yes, time for the new ball. Pakistan's chance to finish the day on a high! And Shaheen Shah Afridi is back here. 16-4-42-1 are his figures so far.
On off, blocked out.
In that fourth stump channel on a good length, Kane punches this one to covers and denies the single on this occasion.
On middle, nudged to deep square leg for a single.
Outside off, Henry walks to the off stump and blocks this one out.
A length delivery again wide outside off, Nicholls strikes this one to the deep cover region. A brace.
On a length outside the off pole, Henry raises his bat and watches this sail into Rizwan's mitts.
Mohammad Abbas is back here. 17-6-32-1 are his figures so far. This is the last over before the second new ball.
The sweep is out again. Tossed up delivery on off, Henry gets down and sweeps it behind square on the leg side for a single.
On off, bunted down to long on for a single.
Short and on off, Williamson rocks back and taps it to wide mid on this time.
Short and outside off, Kane backs away and strokes it to cover. Says 'no' for a single.
On the pads, nudged to short mid-wicket off the back foot.
Loopy on off, blocked to the off side.
Outside off, well left by Henry Nicholls.
Good length ball outside off, dabbed towards point for one. Good bowling this from Faheem. Needs to be backed up with good fielding as well.
Full and outside off, seaming in after pitching, Kane Williamson watches and then lets it be.
Fullish and outside off, Kane leaves it alone. That is good there. Bowl it away from Williamson.
Full and around the off pole line, nudged down to mid off for a quick single.
Fullish and outside off, left alone by Nicholls. They are bowling it wide outside off to both the batters here. Planning to take the ball away from the range of the batters.
He is using the sweep to good effect, Henry. Around off, he sweeps this towards fine leg for one.
Loopy ball on the off pole, Kane pushes it down to long off for one this time.
Looped up on off, pushed to cover.
Loopy delivery on the off pole line, blocked back to the spinner.
Zafar Gohar floats this outside off, the reverse paddle is out. It goes to Alam at third man and results in a single.

Floats this outside off, Kane goes inside out through the covers, through the carpet. Takes a single and it will bring up the 200-run partnership between these two. They love batting with each other, this pair.
Fullish and well outside off from Faheem Ashraf again, Nicholls does not go chasing after that one.
Full and outside off, left alone.
Full and well outside off again, this time, Henry is not tempted to play at that. Leaves it alone.
Full and well outside off, Henry Nicholls looks to slash that over covers. Misses.
Similar delivery, this time, he lets it be.
Full and well outside off, Nicholls goes chasing after that, only to miss.
Floats this on the off pole, bunted down to mid on this time.
Floated on off, blocked to mid off.

NOT OUT! When it is going your way, it is going your way. The crowd is happy. On off, Nicholls rocks back and taps it to mid-wicket. He calls for a quick single and Williamson runs to the other end, the danger end. The fielder there has a shy at the stumps and he hits the bulls eye as well and there is an appeal for a run out. The umpires take it upstairs to have a look. Hmm... the bails are not dislodged properly there and Williamson is in by the time it is properly dislodged. So, Kane stays. And a single.
Is that a run out? Is Williamson gone? He does not look happy. Let's see what the replays have to show though. WELL, HE HAS SURVIVED THAT!
The reverse paddle is out. He has played that really well here, Henry. Gets it to the right of third man and gets two.
On off, blocked to the leg side.
Floated on off, Henry strokes it aerially over mid-wicket. 'Catch it' is the call but it goes well over the fielder who backtracks. A couple.

DROPPED! Another chance for Shan, but it goes begging. Tough chance though. Short and outside off, Williamson cuts that. It goes to the right of Masood at gully, where he stretches to grab that but fails to hold on.
Shortish and outside off, Kane chops it down to mid off, off the pitch.
FOUR! Well wide from Ashraf. And the New Zealand skipper obliges. Cuts it wide of gully and gets a boundary. A remarkable time to be a NZ cricket fan. To see the captain performing like this.
Faheem lands this one on a good length around off, it pitches and nips back in. KW though watchfully leaves it alone.
Another one in the channel outside off, Kane Williamson goes after that one but ends up missing it.
This one is outside off as well but well within the tramline this time, Williamson lets it be.
WIDE! On a good length but way outside off, Kane was initially interested in playing at that but then ends up leaving it. It was past the tramline and hence wide called.
That one misses everything! Slower through the air and outside off, Henry looks to play that on the off side but he misses.
Slower in the air on off stump, HN gets down and sweeps it to the right of deep backward square leg. A brace. At the moment, every ball is going for runs here.
That is a good shot. Clever. Gohar tosses this on the off pole line, the reverse sweep is out. It goes to the right of third man and results in two.
Tosses this on the off pole, Henry Nicholls prods forward and keeps it out.
Short and on the off pole, Nicholls rocks back and taps it to the on side.
Tossed up on off, Henry gets down and sweeps to the leg side but it hits short leg and results in a dot.

FOUR! THERE IT IS! 24TH TEST TON FOR WILLIAMSON! Shortish and on the pads, Kane Williamson tickles it down towards fine leg. The fielder there runs to his right but cannot cut it off. A boundary results. 100 in just 140 balls.
Full and on middle and leg, Williamson looks to flick that but ends up getting a safe leading edge to mid off. A dot. Nervous crowd here, on Williamson.
FOUR! 250 up for New Zealand. KW moves to 99. It is his highest score at Hagley Oval. Just had so much time there. Short ball, Kane pulls this through mid-wicket for a boundary.
Cutting and cut away. Short and outside off, cut to deep point, but just for one.
Outside off, left alone.
Nicholls works this to mid-wicket for a couple.
Naseem Shah was hammered for 4 boundaries in the last over and that has forced a bowling change. Faheem Ashraf is on now. 14-3-37-1 to him so far.
Single taken on the last ball of the over. 245/3. On off, pushed down to long on for a single.
On the shorter side on off and middle, Henry camps back and pushes it to cover.
Zafar loops this on off and middle, Kane Williamson bunts this down to mid on for a run. Moves to 95.
Looped up on off, swept to deep backward square leg for one.
Flatter ball on off, Henry Nicholls goes back and keeps it out.
Loopy ball outside off, Henry gets down and sweeps but finds mid-wicket there. Williamson sends Nicholls back, on the single.

FOUR! Ends the over with a boundary as well! 16 runs off this over. Williamson moves to 94 with this shot as well, closing in on a fantastic century. A full ball around off, Kane drives this one nicely through the mid on region and the timing on this will ensure that the ball meets the ropes.
Back of a length ball and around off, Kane blocks this.

FOUR! Another classy stroke by Captain Kane! He looks to be in some mood after the Drinks break! Another good length ball around off, Kane whips this one through the mid-wicket region to find the ropes again.
On off, well kept out by Kane.

EDGY FOUR! Williamson gets one more. Not how he wanted to play that but the result is what he will be pleased with! A short of a length ball, Kane looked to block this one away but the ball takes the edge and flies through the slips into the third man region for a boundary.

FOUR! CLASS! Williamson has no fatigue even though he has been out here for a long time! A full length ball on middle, Williamson flicks this one nonchalantly through the mid-wicket region to find the ropes.

DRINKS! Well, there seems to be no stopping this partnership between Kane and Henry here. It has gone past 150 and is showing no signs of relenting at all. The deficit for New Zealand is now 71 and Pakistan need wickets, and need to take them quickly. Let's see if they can first break this partnership, after the mini-break...
Dot to end. Floated on off, Nicholls keeps this one out.
On off, blocked out.
Three now! Short and on middle, Williamson pulls this one to the deep square leg region for three runs.
Short and outside off, Kane cuts this one through point and picks up a couple.
On off, kept out by KW.
On off, pushed to covers.

NOT OUT! This would not be out but they had to go for it. On a good length and around middle and leg, Henry looks to tuck this one away but misses to get hit on the pads. The players appeal but no says the umpire. It does not look like Rizwan will take the review but at the last moment, he goes for it. The verdict is in and the ball was pitching outside the leg stump. Pakistan lose their review and the on-field decision will stay on.
Pakistan review! Rizwan takes the review at the last moment. Looked to be outside leg and the verdict is the same. Pitching outside leg. They lose their review.

150-RUN PARTNERSHIP UP. What a partnership this has been for the Kiwis. Just what they needed. Brilliant batting from these two. Outside off, cut away by the skipper to the deep point region for one run.
On off, Kane defends this one.
A full ball on the pads, tickled to the right of fine leg and it looked like the ball would meet the ropes. But the man there, runs to his right, dives and keeps this down just to two runs.
On middle, worked to the leg side.
Well driven but well fielded too! On a length on off, Kane drives this to the cover region where the fielder does well to stop this one.
Tossed up and around off, Henry gets on his knees and sweeps this one to the deep mid-wicket region to pick up a brace.
On off, blocked out.
Short again and outside off, Henry looks to cut this one away, but the ball spun back in and took the inside edge, bounces and goes to Rizwan.
Short and on middle, KW swivels and pulls this one through mid-wicket and Shaheen does well to stop the ball before the ropes. Three runs.
On off, Kane pushes this to mid on.
Floated on off, blocked out.
On off, blocked to the leg side.
Overpitched and around off, Williamson drives this one to the mid off fielder and the batters scamper through for the quick single.
On the pads, Nicholls clips this one to fine leg for a single.
A good length ball and on off, Nicholls plays this one back to the bowler.
On a length outside off, Henry shoulders arms this this one.
On off, worked to point.
On off, HN works it through mid on to collect a single.
On off, blocked.

An appeal for a catch but no says the umpire. Flatter and on middle, Nicholls looks to tuck it away but misses. The ball takes the pads and the man at short leg takes the catch. There is an appeal but no says the umpire. Came off the pad, this.
Flatter and outside off, HN cuts this to point for just a dot.
FOUR! Innovation at the fore now! Nicholls looks very comfortable out in the middle. Flighted and on middle, Henry gets on his knees and reverse sweeps this one through point and he finds the ropes.
Flatter and on middle, Henry tucks this to mid-wicket.
On off, KW keeps this one out.
FOUR! The skipper dispatches this one! Short and wide outside off, Williamson gets on top of the bounce and cuts this one through the point region to find the ropes.
On off, blocked.
NO BALL. Oh dear, another No Ball. Somebody needs to have a chat with this young pacer as he is bowling a lot of No Balls. He has overstepped his line again. Outside off, cut to point for one.
On off, kept out.
NO BALL. Another length ball, but this time, just outside off, punched to covers for one. But hang on.. the umpire signals a No Ball as Naseem has overstepped again. Poor stuff from the youngster.
On a length and on off, well kept out by Kane.
A full ball on middle, Kane clips this one through the square leg region and will pick up a couple of runs.
Naseem Shah is back on. 10-1-41-0 are his numbers so far.
On a length and outside off, left alone.
Shortish and outside off, Henry Nicholls opens the face of his bat and guides that through backward point. Two is the call and two they get.
Full and just outside the off pole, Nicholls taps it down to mid off.
Good length ball around off, Henry defends it.
Short ball, around off, Henry drags it down to short mid-wicket.
Full and outside off, pushed down to mid off for a quick one.

An appeal for LBW but not given. Floats this around off, Henry strides forward to block but misses and gets hit on the top of his pads. An appeal but it results in vain. Perhaps struck him outside the line there.
Full and around off, blocked back to the bowler.
FOUR! Swept well. Good manipulation from Henry here. Floated on off, Henry gets down and sweeps it through short fine leg, wide of the fielder there, and gets a boundary.

Flighted ball outside off, Nicholls gets down and sweeps it hard, through square leg. Takes on the fielder in the deep and gets two runs. Gets to his 50 and it is his 11th in Tests. Playing in tandem with his skipper here. Tough runs and he has earned them well.
Flatter ball on the pads, Nicholls nudges it through square leg. Nice piece of timing. Picks up two.
Floated outside off, stroked through the covers for a single.
Zafar Gohar is back. 2-0-8-0 are his numbers so far.
Full and outside off, Henry gets across and defends it to the leg side for a dot.
Full and around off, defended down to mid on.

In the air... but safe. Some work for Naseem to do. And the hosts get three. Short ball, Kane Williamson goes for the pull shot but ends up getting it off the bottom part of the blade. It goes wide of the man at mid on and goes through mid-wicket for three runs.
Full and outside off, Williamson plays that with soft hands towards gully.

FOUR! Ohh.. excellent shot. That was some shot. Short ball, around the off pole, Williamson just swivels a little in his crease and pulls that in front of square on the leg side and sends it to the deep mid-wicket fence.
Short and outside off, seaming in after pitching, Kane watches it go all the way to Rizwan.
Good piece of fielding. Short and outside off, Henry cuts it in front of the man at point, who dives and keeps it out.
Good length ball on off, defended to mid on.
Good length ball on the off stump line, blocked. Another area where Mohammad Abbas can be dangerous.
Length and outside off, left alone. This is where Abbas can be dangerous. He makes you think a lot.

FOUR! Three was the call from Henry Nicholls but they get a boundary. Bonus run, one can say. Bad bowling from Mohammad. He bowls it shortish and on the pads, Henry glances it through square leg. Fawad gives chase but the ball manages to just about trickle into the boundary.
Full and around the off stump, defended to the off side. The keeper has come up to the stumps now.
Short and outside off, cut away to deep point. A single to finish the over.
Length ball outside the off pole line, Nicholls gets across and defends it out.
Length delivery around the off pole, Henry jumps and keeps it out back on the track.
Ohh... cut him into half there. Shortish and just outside off, HN jumps and looks to play at that but the ball goes past his inside edge here, to the keeper.

FOUR! The 100-run partnership comes up between these two! Pulled away. What a shot from Nicholls. Short ball, Henry Nicholls swivels and pulls it down to fine leg for a boundary. One of the most vital partnerships for the Kiwis, this.
Outside off, Henry shoulders arms.
Faheem Ashraf is back. 11-3-22-1 are his figures so far. Can he provide a breakthrough here?
Shortish and on the pads, Kane tucks it to deep backward square leg and takes a couple. Gets to his 33rd Test match 50 with that. Just continuing his good form, isn't he?
Good length ball on the stumps, the New Zealand skipper stands tall and defends it out.
Angles in a full ball on the stumps, the New Zealander is solid in his defence.
Fullish and just outside off, KW defends it back to Mohammad Abbas.
On a length, outside off, stabbed to the man at point.
On a length and outside off, defensively pushed to the man at cover-point. A 'no' follows.
Fullish and around off, defended to the leg side off the inner half.
Shortish and on the off pole line, Kane Williamson gets across and flicks it to fine leg for one. Hang on... the umpire signals leg byes. So, it came off the pads.
Short ball, around the off stump line, Williamson sits under that one.
Length and around the off stump, pushed back to the bowler.

EDGED AND FOUR! Gets the outside edge.... but it goes flying through. Length delivery outside off, Kane looks to defend but gets an outside edge there. Squared him up. It goes in the gap between slips and gully and to the third man region for a boundary. They need to put an extra fielder there, Pakistan.
Length ball outside off, Kane gets across and fends it out. Says no to Henry for a single.
Abbas angles in a length ball on the off pole line, Henry Nicholls looks to tuck it on the leg side but misses and it comes off his pads, and goes to the on side.
Outside off, left alone.
Length delivery around the off pole line, defensively nudged to short mid-wicket. A 'no' follows again.
Good length ball outside off, Nicholls moves across and defends it out to mid on. Rizwan says 'bowling, well bowled'.
Full and outside off, left alone.
Good length ball outside off, Henry gets across and taps it to the leg side. Says 'no' to his captain, for a single.
Full and outside off, Kane Williamson gets across and blocks it out.
Very full and outside off, jammed out to mid on. Williamson says 'no' to the single.
Good length ball outside off, left alone. Kane is a difficult batsman to bowl to.
Full and around the off pole, Henry pushes it straight back. It hits the stumps at the other end and deflects to mid on. New Zealand sneak in a single.
Good length ball around off, defended to the off side.
FOUR! Straying this time. Too good for that. On the pads of Henry Nicholls, he tickles it down to the fine leg boundary with ease. Too easy for Nicholls there.
Fullish and around off, tapped to short mid-wicket for a quick single.
Good length ball angled into the off pole line, blocked.

An appeal for a caught behind but not given. Hmm.... Pakistan do not opt to review that. There was some sound there. Good length ball just outside the off pole line, Henry stands tall and looks to defend. But he misses and there is some sound as the ball goes past his outside edge and Rizwan takes it. Maybe the boot just scraped the pitch there.
Good length ball angled into the off pole line, defended to the off side. A 'no' from Henry follows.
Shortish and outside the off pole, Williamson rocks back and pulls it in front of square on the on side. Mid-wicket gives chase and keeps it out. Three taken though.
Good length ball outside off, Kane defends it.
Short and outside off, HN hops and punches that between backward point and cover-point. Takes two runs.
Good length ball around off, defended to mid on. A 'no' follows.
Short and outside off, Henry Nicholls looks to cut but ends up chopping it to the keeper, off his bottom part of bat.
Around off, Nicholls taps it back to the bowler.
Shortish and around off, Henry jumps and keeps it out.
Fullish and on middle, tucked to short mid-wicket. The fielder there misfields, conceding a single. And that brings up the 150 for New Zealand.
Shaheen Afridi is back from the other end at the Hagley Oval. 13-4-30-1 are his numbers so far.
Good length ball outside off, defended to the leg side.
Full and outside off from Mohammad, Nicholls leaves it alone again.
In the channel outside off, Henry shoulders arms.
Good length ball outside off, left alone.
FOUR! This one is cut away wide. A bit of a loosener. Short and outside off, Henry cuts it through backward point and obtains a boundary.
Shortish and outside off, Henry cuts but finds point there.

Right, we are all set to get underway with the last session then. The umpires stride out to the middle and the Pakistan players are in a huddle near the ropes. Done with the same, they take their respective positions on the field. Following them are Kane Williamson and Henry Nicholls. Mohammad Abbas will begin with the ball here. Let's play say the umpires, and we are underway...
... Day 2, Session 3...

After losing Taylor early in the session, Kane and Nicholls decided to steady the ship and were patient with their work. They even got to their 50-run stand and are looking quite good and solid out there. They will be looking to battle it out in the last session and add as many runs as they can, without suffering a lot of casualties. Which team takes the final session? Will the hosts continue their good work with the blade in hand or will the visitors show their might with the ball? All the answers after the Tea Break. Join us at 1600 local (0300 GMT).

The Kiwis were on the back foot at the start of the session as some brilliant work by Abbas, saw him scalp the wicket of Taylor. Him and Shaheen were bowling really good and Shaheen also picked up the wicket of Nicholls but he had overstepped his line and that would be a No Ball and Henry survived. The bowling has been good but they have not been rewarded with wickets and that is what they will be looking to do in the last session.

Another session where the hosts go back feeling content with the work that they have done. They have not been on the charge but have done well to fend off the attack of the Pakistani pacers and would be pleased with how things have panned out.
On middle, pushed back to the bowler. THAT WILL BE TEA ON DAY 2!

IN THE AIR..SHORT! They could have got the big wicket of Kane Williamson but it was not meant to be. Flatter and on off, Williamson looks to tuck this one away to the leg side but it comes off the lower part of the blade and goes towards the fielder at mid-wicket but the ball lands short of the man there.
On off, blocked out.
Floated on off, Kane works this to covers.
Short and outside off, Nicholls cuts this one to deep point for a single.
Flatter and on middle, worked to the leg side for one.
Flatter and on middle, punched back to Zafar. Just the one run off Gohar's second over.
On middle, tucked to the leg side.
Flighted on off, Henry skips down the track and pushes it back to Gohar.
Loopy and around off, Kane works this one through mid on to rotate the strike.
Flighted and on middle, Kane pushes this back to the bowler.
Floated on off, pushed to covers.
On middle, worked to the leg side.
Outside off, Kane slashes this one to deep point for a single.

FOUR! Back-to-back boundaries for Kane and he moves to 37 now. Changes the length this time and bowls a full ball on middle, Williamson tucks this one through the mid-wicket region to find the ropes. KW pouncing on Shan here.
FOUR! Williamson does not miss out on these! Slightly shorter and around off, Kane swivel-pulls this one through the diving fielder at mid-wicket and the ball runs away to the ropes.
Back of a length and around off, Henry slashes this one through point to pick up a single.
Outside off, left alone.
FOUR! Ends the over on a good note, does Kane! Flighted and around off, Williamson skips down the track and lofts this one over the fielder at mid on and the ball runs away to the ropes.
Flighted on off, Kane is solid in his defense.
Goes short and outside off this time, Nicholls rocks back and punches this one through covers to pick up three runs.
Same delivery as the last ball, Henry blocks it out again.
Loopy and around off, HN blocks this one out.
Floated on off, well kept out.
Zafar Gohar, the debutant, is in to bowl now.
On middle, nudged to the leg side. 7 runs off Masood's first over.
Full ball on middle, Kane, again clips this one through square leg for a couple of runs.
On middle, nudged to the deep square leg region for a brace.

On a length and around off, Williamson looked to block this one out but the ball takes the outside edge and goes through the gully region and the batters collect three runs. This also brings up the 50-run partnership between these two. The Kiwis needed this and these both have done well to deliver so far.
Outside off, left alone again.
On a length and outside off, HN leaves this one alone.
Shan Masood is introduced into the attack.
On off, blocked to the leg side.
On off, blocked out well. 'No' is the call for the single, by Kane.
Short of a length and around off, pulled through mid-wicket for another single.
On off, worked to the mid on region for a quick run.
On a length and on middle, tucked to the square leg region.
On off, guided to the gully fielder.
On off, solid in defense, is Henry.
Full and on off, pushed back to the bowler.
Another bouncer on off, HN leaves it alone. Also, Naseem has overstepped. Will be a No Ball.
Bouncer on middle, HN sits this one out.

FOUR! Not what Nicholls was looking to do, but as long as the boundaries come, he won't care. On a shorter length on middle, Henry moves to the leg side and looks to slash this one away but the ball takes the top edge and goes over the keeper's head into the fine leg fence for a boundary.
Another bouncer on middle and off, HN ducks under this one.
Bouncer on middle, Henry sits under this one.

5 WIDES. Too short and this will be a wide and a boundary. This one is around off, Henry leaves it alone because it is too short, Rizwan tries to hop to grab this one but misses. The ball runs away to the third man fence. Wided too, by the umpire.
On a length and on off, well kept out by Williamson.
On off, blocked.
An appeal for caught behind but turned down. On a length and around off, Kane looks to pad this one away but it takes the pad and goes to Rizwan. They go up in appeal but the umpire says no.
On middle, tucked to square leg.
Length and on off, Kane works this to mid on and denies the single this time.
On off, pushed to the leg side.

What a great last ball! He bowls a yorker on off, Henry sorts his feet out and looks to push at this but misses and the ball whizzes past his outside edge, also past the off pole, into Rizwan's mitts. There is an appeal for caught behind but no says the umpire.
Short and outside off this time, cut away but finds the point fielder.
Short one around off, HN, again does not attempt any shot to this.
On off, worked towards the mid on region.
NO BALL. Short one again around off, HN sways away from the line of the ball. Also, Naseem had overstepped and hence, this will be a No Ball.
Short one around off, Henry, first, was looking to play at that, but seeing the bounce that was generated, thought better and let this one go.
Length on middle, HN pushes it back to Naseem.
Short of a length and around the middle pole, helped to the fine leg region for a single.
Full ball again outside off, pushed to covers.
BEATEN. Oooohhh....that's a good delivery! Short of a length and around off, Nicholls looks to block this one out but gets beaten.
WIDE. Way too short and outside off, Henry leaves it alone. Wided.
Third delivery in a row which is full and outside off, Henry, again does not think too much in leaving this one alone.
Same delivery as the last ball, another leave by Nicholls.
Full and outside off, Henry watchfully sees this one go to the keeper.
Short of a length and around off, KW is solid in blocking this one out.
On off, punched to covers.
Length and around off, solid push to the gully region by Williamson.
Short and around off, Kane punches this one through the cover-point region for a brace.
A length delivery on middle, Kane tucks this to mid on and looks for the run but decides not to, in the end.
Full and around off, KW pushes it back towards Naseem.
Outside off, HN does not engage.
On off, blocked out.
On middle, KW tucks this one, just past the leg gully fielder, to the fine leg region for one.

FOUR! Beautifully played by Williamson and he gets a boundary! Overpitches this around off and middle, Kane plays this with a straight bat through the mid on region and the ball runs away to the ropes. 100 up for the Kiwis as well. They still trail by 197 runs.
Outside off, left alone.
On middle, worked to the square leg region.

DRINKS. The game is at the balance in the moment but the visitors will be the happier side heading into this mini break. They have bowled really well and have done well to get rid of Taylor and almost sent back Nicholls to the hut, if it was not for the No Ball. More of the same, is what they will be thinking. The Kiwis, on the other hand, are on the back foot slightly and Williamson and Nicholls will need to stitch a good partnership now.
Outside off, left alone.
EDGY FOUR! Lucky again, is Nicholls. A short of a length ball on off, Henry looks to block this one out but the ball takes the inside edge and runs away to the fine leg region for a boundary.
Outside off, left alone.
On off, blocked out.
NO BALL. Naseem oversteps and this will be a No Ball. Short of a length and around off, Kane rocks back on his back foot and punches this one through covers to pick up three runs.
Another length delivery on off, Williamson works this to point and denies the single.
On off, KW guides it to gully.
Another length ball outside off, another leave by Henry.
Length outside off, Nicholls sees no reason to have a poke at this.
Outside off, left alone.
On middle, nudged to square leg for one.
Outside off, Henry pushes this to point for a single.
Outside off, Nicholls does not attempt any shot to this one.
Faheem Ashraf is back into the attack. 6-2-11-1 are his numbers so far.
Outside off, left alone.
Back of a length and on off, Williamson pushes this to mid on.
Length and outside off this time, Kane just leaves it.
Outside off, KW thinks about playing at this, but pulls out at the last moment.
Goes fuller this time, around off, Kane punches this one to the cover region but finds the man there.
Length and on off, played towards the point region.
Naseem Shah is back on. 5-0-20-0 are his figures so far.
Length ball outside off, Nicholls punches this one to covers but finds Faheem there.
Back of a length on off, Nicholls pushes this back to Abbas.
On off, pushed to point.
Outside off, Nicholls lets this one be.

FOUR LEG BYES. Abbas strays from his length and gets punished! Bowls this fuller and on the pads, Henry looks to tuck this one away but misses and the ball takes the pads and goes past the keeper, into the fine leg region for a boundary.
Outside off, left alone by Henry.
On off, tapped to point. 1 run off the over.
Outside off, left alone.
Shaheen comes around the wicket this time and bowls a length ball outside off, Kane shoulders arms to this one.
Length ball outside off, Kane raises his blade to let this one through to the keeper.
On off, played towards covers for a single.
Outside off, Henry does not engage on this occasion.
On off, blocked out.

FOUR! Williamson plays it late and fetches a boundary! Short of a length and outside off, Kane watches the ball, hops on time and gets on top of the bounce to punch this one through cover-point for a boundary.
On off, pushed towards mid off. 'No', says Kane again, for the run.
In that channel around off and on a good length, Williamson blocks this one out and says 'no' to the single.
Outside off, Kane leaves this one alone.
On off, well blocked by Kane.

EDGED...SHORT! Henry survives again! On a length and around off, Nicholls again looks for the block away but the ball takes the outside edge and goes to the right of gully, who is not able to get his hands under the ball and the ball goes towards the third man region. The batters see this opportunity and sneak in a couple of runs.
Good length and outside off, Henry leaves this one nicely.
Outside off, left alone.
On middle, blocked.

NO BALL. This was out but Shaheen has overstepped which will mean that Nicholls survives and gets another life. This is on a length and around off, Henry looks to keep this one out but misses and the ball takes the outside edge and goes to the left of Rizwan, who dives and takes it very nicely. But wait...the umpire's want to check if this is a No Ball and it is. Woah. A good wicket and catch, but disappointment for the visitors.
On off, pushed to the mid off region. They think about the single but Kane says no, in the end.
Bowls this on a length and on the pads, clipped to the right of fine leg for a couple of runs.
Down the leg side, KW misses his flick away.
Nicholls opens his account for this game! On a length outside off, pushed to the cover region for a single.
On off, well kept out.
Length ball outside off, Henry leaves this one alone.
On off, pushed to the mid-wicket region.
Length on middle, pushed to the leg side.
Another maiden by Shaheen as Kane leaves this good length ball around off alone.
Short of a length and around off, tapped to point. Again, Kane thinks about the single but then decides not to go.
On a length and around off, Kane pushes this to the mid off region. 'WAITTTTTT', says Kane, for the single.
On a length outside off, Kane is not interested in playing at this.
Bouncer on off, Williamson sways away from the line of the ball.

We are back for the Second session of Day 2. The batters for Kiwis, Kane Williamson and Ross Taylor stride out into the middle, followed by the Pakistani players, who are spreading out on the field. Mohammad Abbas to start off after Lunch. Here he comes....
... Day 2, Session 2 ...

Right then, Williamson and Taylor would look to now stitch another good partnership and steer the ship to safer shores. Meanwhile, Pakistan though, would look to breathe down the New Zealanders' necks, after the break. Who will have their say? Join us at around 1340 Local (0040 GMT) to find out...

So, what then looked to be a comfortable session for the Kiwis, soon became nervy with the loss of 2 quick wickets. But Williamson and Taylor steered them to safety in the end, towards Lunch. Shaheen Afridi and Faheem Ashraf have done well to get a wicket each. Mohammad Abbas bowled well but is wicketless so far. He will be looking for one, after the Lunch break.

The day started off with New Zealand getting off to a solid start. Their openers were looking in extremely good touch, they had seen off the first hour well and seemed to be looking to go into Lunch, for the loss of no wickets. But the change of bowling worked for Pakistan. First, Ashraf got the wicket of Blundell, off a LBW review. Then Afridi came back and got the wicket of Tom Latham.

Well, New Zealand would be happy that they managed to see off the session unscathed, after losing their openers. But it will be the Men in Green who would be very happy with their efforts. They got both the openers quickly and the hosts still trail them by 231 runs.

FOUR! Driven straight. Nice way to finish for Ross Taylor and New Zealand ahead of Lunch. RT will feel confident with that shot. Straight down the ground. Full and on the off pole line, Rosco drives it through the ground, wide of the bowler and mid off, and bags a boundary. THAT WILL BE LUNCH ON DAY 2!

Play and a miss! Ah... that was the one there. Nicely bowled from Shaheen. Angles it across the right-hander, Ross Taylor does not transfer his weight forward, just throws his hand at it. Misses. Almost nicked it though.
